tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function, and high chloride. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance, indicating possible diabetic nephropathy or another renal pathology, though HbA1c is unexpectedly low. No evidence of urinary infection. Recommend clinical correlation for renal impairment, review of diabetes status, and further nephrological evaluation.
